article.headline: Appalachian St. 76, W. Carolina 65
article.story: CULLOWHEE, N.C. (AP) -- Nate Cranford led three players in double figures as Appalachian State defeated Western Carolina 76-65 on Monday. Cranford had 16 points on 4-of-5 shooting from the three-point range. Demetrius Scott had 13 points, and D.J. Thompson scored 10 points for the Mountaineers (22-6, 13-3 Southern Conference). Nick Aldridge led Western Carolina (10-18, 7-10) with 29 points and 14 rebounds. The Mountaineers led 39-24 at halftime. The Catamounts began chipping away at Appalachian State's lead four minutes into the second half with a 19-8 run that pulled them within 53-48 with 8:32 left. The Mountaineers' Ryann Abraham responded with a 3-pointer to key an 11-4 run that put Appalachian State ahead 64-52 with 5:45 left, and their lead never fell into single digits for the rest of the game.
